  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the sous-vide machine to 130 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Season the lamb shoulder with smoked paprika, cumin, coriander, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat and sear the lamb shoulder until browned on all sides.",
    "Place the lamb shoulder in a sous-vide bag with the garlic and ginger, and seal the bag.",
    "Cook the lamb shoulder in the sous-vide machine for 48 hours.",
    "Remove the lamb shoulder from the bag and slice it into thin strips.",
    "Serve the lamb shoulder on a slate tile, garnished with fresh parsley and a side of steamed vegetables."
